com.google.android.droiddriver.actions

Interface Action

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AccessibilityAction, AccessibilityClickAction, AccessibilityClickAction.DoubleClick, AccessibilityClickAction.LongClick, AccessibilityClickAction.SingleClick, AccessibilityScrollAction, BaseAction, ClickAction, ClickAction.DoubleClick, ClickAction.LongClick, ClickAction.SingleClick, EventAction, KeyAction, SingleKeyAction, SwipeAction, TextAction

    public interface Action
    Interface for performing action on a UiElement. An action is a high-level user interaction that can be performed in various ways, for example, via synthesized events, or the Accessibility API.

    • Method Detail

      • perform

        boolean perform(UiElement element)
        Performs the action.
        Parameters:
        element - the Ui element to perform the action on
        Returns:
        Whether the action is successful. Some actions throw exceptions in case of failure, when that behavior is more appropriate. For example, if event injection returns false.

      • getTimeoutMillis

        long getTimeoutMillis()
        Gets the timeout to wait for an indicator that the action has been carried out. Different DroidDriver implementations use this value in different ways. For example, UiAutomationDriver waits for AccessibilityEvent up to this value. InstrumentationDriver ignores this value because it synchronizes on the event loop.

      • toString

        String toString()

        It is recommended that this method return the description of the action, for example, "SwipeAction{DOWN}".

        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
